Executive Profile
Samuel   Valenti IIIPresident, CEO, Chief Investment Officer, and Chairman, World Capital Partners L.L.C.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 8 Board Members in 8 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships71--
Background

		Mr. Samuel Valenti, III, also known as Sam, serves as the Chairman, Chief Executive Officer, President and Chief Investment Officer of Valenti Capital LLC and World Capital Partners L.L.C. Mr. Valenti serves as Senior Advisor to GreenLeaf Trust Bank. He serves as a Co-Founder and Managing Partner at V5 Partners. Mr. Valenti served as the President of Masco Capital Corporation since 1988 until 2008. He served as Senior Executive, Corporate Officer and veteran of Masco ... Corporation from 1968 to 2008. He served as an Executive Chairman of TriMas Corporation from November 2005 to November 2008. He served as Senior Managing Director and Partner of Heartland Industrial Partners, L.P. and its Special Advisor until November 2005. He served as Vice President of Investments of Masco Corp. from May 1974 to October 1998 and Senior Executive and Corporate Officer from May 1977 to October 1998. He served as an Advisor of Financial Services & Insurance for TMX Communications Inc. He was Leader for over 25 years of a team of investment professionals involved in a wide array of investment activities including stock and bond investment, commodity hedging, merger and acquisition analysis and venture capital investing. He has been the Chairman of Trimas Corporation since June 2002. He serves as Chairman of Masco Corp. He serves as a Director of American Axle Corporation and TriMas Corporation. He has been an Independent Director of American Axle & Manufacturing Holdings Inc. since October 31, 2013. He has been Director at American Axle & Manufacturing, Inc. since 2013. He serves on the Advisory Boards of Questor, Long Point, Doll Capital and Camelot. He served as a Co-Chair of the Board at Horizon Global Corporation from June 29, 2015 to June 30, 2016 and has been its Director since June 22, 2015. He served as the Chairman of Business Leaders for Michigan and serves as its Director. He served as a Director of Oldco M Corporation from November 28, 2000 to July 2006 and Masco Corp. from 1988 to March 2008. Mr. Valenti served as a Director of Collins & Aikman LLC and Collins & Aikman Products LLC from February 2001 to September 2004; Metaldyne Corp. from November 28, 2000 to July 11, 2006 and Arbor Drugs, Inc. since 1992. He served as a Director of Masco Capital Corp. from 1988 to March 2008. He served as Chairman of the Investment Advisory Board of the $50 billion State of Michigan retirement system. Mr. Valenti is one of the 80 members of the Business Leaders for Michigan. He serves on the Advisory Board at the University of Michigan Business School Zell-Lurie Institute. In his nearly 20 year participation with the Advisory Board, Mr. Valenti spearheaded the State's initial investments in venture capital as well as a broad range of alternative investments. He serves on the Harvard Business School Advisory Council for Global Corporate Governance and the Advisory Council at the University of Notre Dame. He was Director of Children's Hospital and the Center for Creative Studies. Mr. Valenti was Crain's Newsmaker of the Year for 2007; recipient of the 2010 "Spirit of Michigan" award, presented at the Accelerate Michigan Innovation Competition and was presented the 2012 Crain's M&A Lifetime Achievement Award. Mr. Valenti has extensive knowledge and expertise in the management of diversified manufacturing businesses and subject matter expertise in the areas of finance, economics, corporate governance and asset management. Mr. Valenti holds a Masters of Arts degree in Economics, with distinction, from Western Michigan University and a Bachelors of Arts Degree, Magna Cum Laude.Read Full Background




